legends.description: Other Supervisory Devices (Low Pressure, Low Water,

legends_notes.description: Smoke detector sensitivity measurement and cleaning date should be recorded in the remark column.
Status Change, including time delay, should be recorded in the remark column.
Duct smoke detector pressure differential should be confirmed and recorded in the remark column.
Time delay setting of water flow switch should be recorded in the remark column.
Sprinkler supervisory switches cause trouble condition to be annunciated but not an alarm condition.
Upper and lower pressure setting of supervisory devices should be recorded in the remark column.
Low temperature setting should be recorded in the remark column.
Identify the specific ancillary devices in the remark column.

monthly_year_notes.note: 1. National Fire Code of Canada requires that these records be retained a minimum of two (2) years.
2. Tests to be conducted in accordance with this Standard (CAN/ULC-S536) while on emergency power.
3. The monthly test is not required during the month that the annual test is completed.
